<h1>Patterns and Index Cells</h1>
<h3>
James Coplien applied Alexander's theory to the design of software patterns.
<img src="SpaceFinalFronti-1-image-10.gif">
In a software pattern, there are <font color=red>interacting centers</font>. The interaction
can be specified using <b>protocols</b>.

<hr>
From the viewpoint of IC theory, the <b>center</b> can be specified
by an <b>IC cell</b>.  The interaction protocol is specified by
the state transition and message exchange of the IC cells.

<p>
<font color=red>
Therefore from this viewpoint, a software pattern can be specified
as a collection of interacting IC cells, or an IC system.
</font>

